messages.content: What was a positive news story from today?

message.content:
Here are some positive news stories from February 13, 2026:

**International News:**

- **WHO Declares Mpox Outbreak Contained in Central Africa:** The World Health Organization announced that the mpox outbreak in Central African nations is now under control. Intensive vaccination campaigns and improved surveillance systems helped contain the spread, with over 2.5 million vaccine doses administered across affected regions. ([observervoice.com](https://observervoice.com/todays-school-assembly-news-headlines-13-february-2-183444/?utm_source=openai))

- **European Union Announces €10 Billion Green Energy Fund for Developing Nations:** The European Union committed €10 billion to support renewable energy projects in developing countries over the next five years. This initiative aims to help nations transition from fossil fuels to clean energy, with priority given to Africa and Southeast Asian countries. ([observervoice.com](https://observervoice.com/todays-school-assembly-news-headlines-13-february-2-183444/?utm_source=openai))

**Community News:**

- **Community Soccer Match Promotes Positive Change in Pretoria:** In the Itireleng Squatter Camp in Pretoria, South Africa, a community soccer match was organized to motivate both young children and adults to embrace sports as a positive alternative to crime and drug abuse. The event aimed to inspire the community to choose healthier paths and to remind residents that positive change can begin with collective action. ([reutersconnect.com](https://www.reutersconnect.com/item/world-news-february-13-2026/dGFnOnJldXRlcnMuY29tLDIwMjY6bmV3c21sX01UMVpVTUEwMDBFOVVKMjc?utm_source=openai))

**Health and Wellness:**

- **National Donor Day Celebrated at Iowa State Capitol:** Community members and advocates gathered in Des Moines to honor the power of donation. The event highlighted how Iowans make a difference every day through blood, organ, eye, and tissue donation, while also recognizing the many patients still waiting for lifesaving transplants. ([bloodcenter.org](https://www.bloodcenter.org/about/news/blog/feel-good-news--february-13-2026/?utm_source=openai))

These stories highlight significant progress in public health, environmental sustainability, community engagement, and the spirit of giving.
